1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:09,000
Taking walks and playing games when there's sunny weather

2
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:15,000
If there's rain, they're singing songs or reading books together

3
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:21,000
Every day just has a way of feeling extra lucky

4
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:26,000
When you spend it with a friend, just like Bjorn and Bucky

5
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:29,000
Just like Bjorn and Bucky!

6
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:35,000
A northern expedition!

7
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:40,000
This is the life!

8
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:46,000
Nice day we're having!

9
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:48,000
The nicest!

10
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:50,000
It's so hot!

11
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:52,000
Oh my!

12
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:54,000
A great day, right?

13
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:56,000
So very great!

14
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:58,000
So hot!

15
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Perfect day!

16
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:01,000
The best!

17
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:02,000
Huh?

18
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:04,000
Too hot!

19
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:06,000
Bjorn, what's with you?

20
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:07,000
Of course it's hot!

21
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:08,000
It's summer!

22
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:10,000
But in the north it's cold!

23
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:11,000
The whole year round!

24
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:13,000
Nice and cool!

25
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:16,000
Snow and icebergs everywhere!

26
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:17,000
So hey!

27
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:19,000
Maybe you should take a trip up north then!

28
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:20,000
Awesome idea!

29
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:22,000
A northern expedition!

30
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:24,000
But it's a long way away!

31
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:26,000
I'd have to prepare and stuff!

32
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:29,000
We'll get you prepared and stuff!

33
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:30,000
Trust me!

34
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:32,000
I'm an expert at everything!

35
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:33,000
Ha!

36
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:34,000
Ha!

37
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:37,000
You know Bjorn, the north has gotten way norther!

38
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:41,000
It's colder and bleaker and more dangerous here!

39
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:45,000
You'll need warm clothes, good skis, party provisions, and…

40
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:46,000
I don't know…

41
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:48,000
Snow screen cream?

42
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:51,000
The north doesn't mess around, my friend!

43
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:53,000
I'm okay!

44
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:55,000
Bucky?

45
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:58,000
I'm not sure about this trip!

46
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:00,000
I've got your back, Bjorn!

47
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:01,000
You won't go anywhere…

48
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:03,000
Until I've trained you!

49
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:05,000
Just wait…

50
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:08,000
Hang on!

51
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:11,000
Be right with ya!

52
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:15,000
Talk amongst yourselves!

53
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:20,000
Nearly there now!

54
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:30,000
I hope you're excited, cause this is gonna be super duper kaplowie wowie!

55
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:38,000
Everybody, it's my pleasure to present to you at this time…

56
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:43,000
The one-of-a-kind Northern Expedition Simulator Training Gord!

57
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:45,000
Thank you, thank you, thank you very much!

58
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:46,000
Thank you!

59
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:49,000
Woah!

60
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:55,000
I'm not so sure about all this, Bucky!

61
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:57,000
Come on, you'll be fine!

62
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:58,000
Let's go!

63
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:01,000
It can strike at any moment!

64
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:02,000
The whipping wind!

65
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:03,000
The blinding snow!

66
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:05,000
That elemental juggernaut!

67
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:07,000
A northern blizzard!

68
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:11,000
Feel the frigid frozen fury!

69
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:13,000
Haha!

70
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:15,000
Feathers in your face!

71
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:21,000
Try to keep your footing on those slick, slippery slivers scattered on the sea!

72
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:23,000
Northern icebergs!

73
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:25,000
Hey, what are these, Buck?

74
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:28,000
I'm not sure, but the North can be unpredictable!

75
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:30,000
You never know what the North's gonna throw at you next!

76
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:33,000
Dangling tree trunks of icy doom?

77
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:34,000
It could happen!

78
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:40,000
And don't forget the thrilling, deadly majesty of the North's countless snow-covered mountains!

79
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:48,000
Where gravity, physics, and geometry conspire to take you on a pulse-pounding ride that will scare your downy white fur off!

80
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:49,000
Uh, help?

81
00:03:49,000 --> 00:04:00,000
Bucky, I'm not certain that I want to go on this expedition up north!

82
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:02,000
Sure you do!

83
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:03,000
Don't worry!

84
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:06,000
Thanks to me, you're now completely prepared for your northern expedition!

85
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:07,000
Well, gosh!

86
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:09,000
Guess I'll go?

87
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:11,000
Great!

88
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:12,000
Safe travels!

89
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:15,000
Stay warm!

90
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:16,000
Take lots of pictures!

91
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:18,000
Um, so, goodbye, I guess?

92
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:20,000
Yep!

93
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:21,000
Send us a postcard!

94
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:23,000
You could maybe just stay, Bjorn!

95
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:26,000
Is that really an option?

96
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,000
Of course, pal!

97
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:31,000
What does the North have to offer that we don't have right here?

98
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:34,000
Icebergs, snow mountains, penguins, frostbite?

99
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:36,000
We got all that stuff!

100
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:39,000
Actually, why would you want to leave at all?

101
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:42,000
I never really wanted to go at all!

102
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:43,000
Yay!

103
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:44,000
Bjorn's going to stay!

104
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:52,000
Now you have your own north that you can share with friends!

105
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:54,000
Complete with your very own yellow penguin!

106
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:55,000
Penguin!

107
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:03,000
Bucky, you do know penguins only live in the south!

108
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:05,000
Mmm!

109
